reviews.snippet: Be it taste, ambience and presentation, Concu comes with the best in all three.From the humble staff to the aesthetic vibes, this place is perfect for an evening hangout with your friends.We tried the Pasta - Fettuccini Pesto Genovese and the Mushroom Cheese Brioche Sandwich, both of which were flavorful and well-prepared. The Cold Coffee was perfectly balanced, and the Basil Mango Kombucha added a refreshing twist to the meal.Staff members were so sweet and cooperative. Had one of the most delicious cakes.

reviews.snippet: Conçu in Jubilee Hills is pure bliss for dessert lovers and café enthusiasts. The pastries and cakes are absolutely divine—especially the signature Tres Leches and macarons. Every item looks like a piece of art and tastes just as amazing. The ambiance is serene, elegant, and perfect for everything from a quiet coffee to a casual meeting. Their coffee is top-notch, and the savory options are equally impressive. The service is warm and professional, making the entire experience delightful. A must-visit for anyone who appreciates fine desserts and classy café vibes.

reviews.snippet:
I recently had the chance to visit Conch Jubilee Hills, and it’s a hidden gem! Nestled in a cozy spot with minimalistic interiors, it has a soft, inviting vibe that I loved. The desserts were the highlight—especially the cookie croissant, which was my absolute favorite, along with some delicious macarons. While the drinks were just okay, the desserts definitely made up for it.

It’s a great spot to visit in the evening for snacks with friends. The washrooms were clean, and the menu clearly marks vegetarian options, making it easy for everyone. If you’re a dessert lover, this is definitely a place to try! ✨💙

reviews.snippet:
The more I say, the less it is for this place. In my opinion, I've had the best desserts of my life here at Concu, and I'm dead serious.

The food, the service, the atmosphere, everything is perfect. And my oh my the food, *chef's kiss*.

We ordered multiple things from the menu over the course of 2 days and there wasn't one thing that disappointed. They've absolutely nailed the flavors and portions of almost all the recipes.

I wish there were more outlets all over the country, because i would do anything for another bite of that French toast, man. Simply the best.

You can try the desserts as per your palette, but, in my opinion, you should definitely try the Strawberry Basil tres leches. Out. Of. This. World.

The coffee is amazing as well. And as I've said a hundred times above, "They, do not miss".

Kudos to the whole team. 🙌🏻

reviews.snippet:
Conçu Hyderabad is a great spot if you’re craving desserts and looking for a cozy café atmosphere, but there are a few areas that could use some improvement.

Ambience & Vibe: The café has a lovely and warm aesthetic. The décor is tasteful, and it’s a comfortable place to unwind, whether you’re meeting up with friends or spending some quiet time alone. The outdoor seating is pleasant, especially in the evenings, but the indoor space can feel a bit cramped, especially during peak hours. Finding a spot to sit on weekends can be challenging, and it does get noisy, which takes away from the relaxed vibe.

Desserts: The desserts are definitely the highlight here. Conçu has a variety of beautifully crafted pastries, cakes, and tarts, and the quality is consistently good. My personal favorites are the Hazelnut Tart and the Pistachio Éclair, both of which are rich and flavorful. However, while the desserts look gorgeous, I’ve found that some of them can be overly sweet, especially the macarons. A little more balance in the sweetness would make them more enjoyable. Also, the price point feels a bit on the higher side for what you get.

Food Menu: Their savory offerings are decent but nothing extraordinary. The sandwiches and croissants are fresh, but I feel like the options are limited and the taste is fairly standard compared to other cafes in the city. I had the Avocado Toast once, and while it was good, it wasn’t something I’d go out of my way to order again. For a place that shines with desserts, the savory menu could use a bit more variety and flavor.

Coffee & Drinks: Conçu’s coffee is solid, though not exceptional. I’ve had their cappuccino a few times, and while it’s good, it lacks the depth of flavor that you’d expect from a café known for its drinks. Their iced coffees are refreshing, especially the Iced Caramel Coffee, but again, nothing stood out as particularly memorable. If you're a casual coffee drinker, you'll probably enjoy it, but for coffee aficionados, it might not hit the mark.

Service: The service is where Conçu could really improve. The staff are friendly, but during busy hours, it can take quite a while for orders to arrive. On a couple of occasions, I found the wait times for both food and drinks to be longer than expected, and there have been times where my order wasn’t quite right. They are polite and fix things quickly, but the consistency could be better.

Conclusion: Overall, Conçu is a nice café with some standout desserts and a charming atmosphere, but there are a few areas that need refining, especially when it comes to service and pricing. It’s a good place to visit if you’re in the mood for something sweet, but with the growing café culture in Hyderabad, there are several other places that might offer a more well-rounded experience. A solid 4 stars from me!

reviews.snippet:
One of the most premium cafes I've ever visited. We visited on a weekend night. The cafe looked so beautiful with all the lighting and greenery outside. It was packed with people and was very lively. They have outdoor and indoor seating. The inside of the cafe is pleasant with pastel color themes and neat, minimalistic layout.

The desserts here are sure to tempt you. The cookies, pastries, eclairs, mousses all look really well done. The prices are a bit on the higher side, but it is one of the rare times when you feel the food is worth it. The bakery items and desserts are definitely good. Other food items are pretty good too, but didn't find them to be that different from other cafes. Would definitely recommend to people who like bakeries and desserts. Wanna try the chocolate pastries next time!
